This project has a graphify knowledge graph at graphify-out/.

- Before answering architecture or codebase questions, read graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md for god nodes and community structure
- If graphify-out/wiki/index.md exists, navigate it instead of reading raw files
- After substantial backend or shared-package code changes in this session, from the repo root run `python -c "from graphify.watch import _rebuild_code; from pathlib import Path; _rebuild_code(Path('.'))"` (or `python3` where that is the default) to keep the graph current
- After large documentation or plan changes, prefer a full graph refresh in Cursor with `/graphify . --update`
- Use graph queries for focused checks such as:
  - service boundaries and unexpected dependencies
  - who reads or writes a given entity
  - shared-package hotspots / god nodes
  - drift between docs, plan, and actual code structure
- Recommended moments to rely on graphify:
  - before architecture reviews
  - before `/review-step`
  - after major refactors
  - when validating `single-writer`, `reservation-first`, and shared-package boundaries
